    "interpretation": {
        "scoringMethod": "Part A Screening: Count responses in shaded boxes (varies by question). 4 or more shaded responses = symptoms highly consistent with ADHD. Total score: Sum all 18 items (0-72).",
        "partAScreening": "Questions 1-6 form Part A. If 4 or more responses fall in the 'shaded' threshold for each question, ADHD is likely and further investigation is warranted.",
        "partBUsage": "Part B (questions 7-18) provides additional clinical information but is not used for formal screening cutoff.",
        "clinicalNotes": "This is a screening tool, not a diagnostic instrument. A positive screen should be followed by a comprehensive clinical interview including childhood history, impairment assessment, and differential diagnosis."
    },

